4 Thus, turning to its melody,
5 that substance was seen by me to sing,
6 upon which a double light is blended;

19 "According to my infallible judgment,
20 how just vengeance was justly
21 punished, has put you in thought;

22 but I will quickly free your mind;
23 and you listen, for my words
24 will make you aware of a great truth.

25 In order not to submit to the virtue that wills
26 a bridle for his own good, that man who was not born,
27 damning himself, damned all his offspring;

34 Now turn your attention to what is being discussed:
35 this nature, united to its maker,
36 as it was created, was pure and good;

40 Therefore, the punishment that the cross inflicted,
41 if it is measured against the nature that was assumed,
42 never was anything so justly deserved;

46 Therefore, different things came from one act:
47 for God and the Jews, one death was pleasing;
48 because of it, the earth trembled and the heavens opened.

55 You say: "I clearly understand what I hear;
56 but why God willed precisely this way
57 for our redemption is hidden from me".

73 The more something conforms to it, the more it pleases it;
74 for the holy ardor that radiates through everything
75 is more alive in that which is most similar.

79 Only sin is that which disennobles it
80 and makes it dissimilar to the supreme good,
81 so that it is little whitened by its light;

85 Your nature, when it sinned totally
86 in its seed, was removed from these dignities,
87 as from paradise;

100 as much as he intended to go up by disobeying;
101 and this is the reason why man was
102 excluded from being able to make satisfaction for himself.

115 for God was more generous in giving himself
116 to make man sufficient to raise himself up,
117 than if he had only remitted it by himself;

124 You say: "I see water, I see fire,
125 air and earth and all their mixtures
126 come to corruption, and last but a short while;

127 and these things were nevertheless creatures;
128 therefore, if what has been said is true,
129 they should be safe from corruption".

130 The angels, brother, and the pure realm
131 in which you are, can be said to have been created,
132 as they are, in their complete being;

136 The matter that they have was created;
137 the informing power was created
138 in these stars that go around them.

139 The soul of every brute and of plants
140 draws the ray and the motion of the holy lights
141 from potentiated matter;
